{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"What I'd like to start off with is an observation,"},{"time":3000,"text":"which is that if I've learned anything over the last year,"},{"time":5000,"text":"it's that the supreme irony"},{"time":7000,"text":"of publishing a book about slowness"},{"time":9000,"text":"is that you have to go around promoting it really fast."},{"time":12000,"text":"I seem to spend most of my time these days"},{"time":14000,"text":"zipping from city to city, studio to studio,"},{"time":17000,"text":"interview to interview,"},{"time":19000,"text":"serving up the book in really tiny bite-size chunks."},{"time":21000,"text":"Because everyone these days"},{"time":23000,"text":"wants to know how to slow down,"},{"time":25000,"text":"but they want to know how to slow down really quickly. So ..."},{"time":28000,"text":"so I did a spot on CNN the other day"},{"time":30000,"text":"where I actually spent more time in makeup than I did talking on air."},{"time":34000,"text":"And I think that -- that's not really surprising though, is it?"},{"time":36000,"text":"Because that's kind of the world that we live in now,"},{"time":38000,"text":"a world stuck in fast-forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41000,"text":"A world obsessed with speed,"},{"time":43000,"text":"with doing everything faster, with cramming more and more"},{"time":46000,"text":"into less and less time."},{"time":48000,"text":"Every moment of the day feels like"},{"time":50000,"text":"a race against the clock."},{"time":52000,"text":"To borrow a phrase from Carrie Fisher, which is"},{"time":54000,"text":"in my bio there; I'll just toss it out again --"},{"time":56000,"text":"\"These days even instant gratification takes too long.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":59000,"text":"And"},{"time":61000,"text":"if you think about how we to try to make things better, what do we do?"},{"time":63000,"text":"No, we speed them up, don't we? So we used to dial; now we speed dial."},{"time":66000,"text":"We used to read; now we speed read. We used to walk; now we speed walk."},{"time":69000,"text":"And of course, we used to date and now we speed date."},{"time":72000,"text":"And even things that are by their very nature slow --"},{"time":75000,"text":"we try and speed them up too."},{"time":78000,"text":"So I was in New York recently, and I walked past a gym"},{"time":80000,"text":"that had an advertisement in the window for a new course, a new evening course."},{"time":83000,"text":"And it was for, you guessed it, speed yoga."},{"time":86000,"text":"So this -- the perfect solution for time-starved professionals"},{"time":89000,"text":"who want to, you know, salute the sun,"},{"time":91000,"text":"but only want to give over about 20 minutes to it."},{"time":94000,"text":"I mean, these are sort of the extreme examples,"},{"time":96000,"text":"and they're amusing and good to laugh at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98000,"text":"But there's a very serious point,"},{"time":100000,"text":"and I think that in the headlong dash of daily life,"},{"time":103000,"text":"we often lose sight of the damage"},{"time":106000,"text":"that this roadrunner form of living does to us."},{"time":109000,"text":"We're so marinated in the culture of speed"},{"time":112000,"text":"that we almost fail to notice the toll it takes"},{"time":114000,"text":"on every aspect of our lives --"},{"time":116000,"text":"on our health, our diet, our work,"},{"time":118000,"text":"our relationships, the environment and our community."},{"time":121000,"text":"And sometimes it takes"},{"time":123000,"text":"a wake-up call, doesn't it,"},{"time":125000,"text":"to alert us to the fact that we're hurrying through our lives,"},{"time":128000,"text":"instead of actually living them; that we're"},{"time":130000,"text":"living the fast life, instead of the good life."},{"time":132000,"text":"And I think for many people, that wake-up call"},{"time":134000,"text":"takes the form of an illness."},{"time":136000,"text":"You know, a burnout, or eventually the body says,"},{"time":139000,"text":"\"I can't take it anymore,\" and throws in the towel."},{"time":141000,"text":"Or maybe a relationship goes up in smoke"},{"time":143000,"text":"because we haven't had the time, or the patience,"},{"time":145000,"text":"or the tranquility,"},{"time":147000,"text":"to be with the other person, to listen to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"And my wake-up call came when I started"},{"time":151000,"text":"reading bedtime stories to my son,"},{"time":154000,"text":"and I found that at the end of day,"},{"time":156000,"text":"I would go into his room and I just couldn't slow down -- you know,"},{"time":159000,"text":"I'd be speed reading \"The Cat In The Hat.\""},{"time":161000,"text":"I'd be -- you know, I'd be skipping lines here,"},{"time":163000,"text":"paragraphs there, sometimes a whole page,"},{"time":165000,"text":"and of course, my little boy knew the book inside out, so we would quarrel."},{"time":168000,"text":"And what should have been the most relaxing, the most intimate,"},{"time":171000,"text":"the most tender moment of the day,"},{"time":173000,"text":"when a dad sits down to read to his son,"},{"time":176000,"text":"became instead this kind of gladiatorial battle of wills,"},{"time":179000,"text":"a clash between my speed"},{"time":181000,"text":"and his slowness."},{"time":184000,"text":"And this went on for some time,"},{"time":186000,"text":"until I caught myself scanning a newspaper article"},{"time":188000,"text":"with timesaving tips for fast people."},{"time":190000,"text":"And one of them made reference to a series of books called"},{"time":192000,"text":"\"The One-Minute Bedtime Story.\""},{"time":194000,"text":"And I wince saying those words now,"},{"time":197000,"text":"but my first reaction at the time was very different."},{"time":199000,"text":"My first reflex was to say,"},{"time":201000,"text":"\"Hallelujah -- what a great idea!"},{"time":203000,"text":"This is exactly what I'm looking for to speed up bedtime even more.\""},{"time":206000,"text":"But thankfully,"},{"time":208000,"text":"a light bulb went on over my head, and my next reaction was very different,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and I took a step back, and I thought,"},{"time":213000,"text":"\"Whoa -- you know, has it really come to this?"},{"time":215000,"text":"Am I really in such a hurry that I'm prepared"},{"time":217000,"text":"to fob off my son with a sound byte at the end of the day?\""},{"time":221000,"text":"And I put away the newspaper --"},{"time":223000,"text":"and I was getting on a plane -- and I sat there,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and I did something I hadn't done for a long time -- which is I did nothing."},{"time":227000,"text":"I just thought, and I thought long and hard."},{"time":230000,"text":"And by the time I got off that plane, I'd decided I wanted to do something about it."},{"time":233000,"text":"I wanted to investigate this whole roadrunner culture,"},{"time":236000,"text":"and what it was doing to me and to everyone else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239000,"text":"And I had two questions in my head."},{"time":241000,"text":"The first was, how did we get so fast?"},{"time":244000,"text":"And the second is, is it possible,"},{"time":246000,"text":"or even desirable, to slow down?"},{"time":249000,"text":"Now, if you think about"},{"time":251000,"text":"how our world got so accelerated, the usual suspects rear their heads."},{"time":254000,"text":"You think of, you know, urbanization,"},{"time":256000,"text":"consumerism, the workplace, technology."},{"time":259000,"text":"But I think if you cut through"},{"time":261000,"text":"those forces, you get to what might be the deeper"},{"time":264000,"text":"driver, the nub of the question,"},{"time":267000,"text":"which is how we think about time itself."},{"time":269000,"text":"In other cultures, time is cyclical."},{"time":272000,"text":"It's seen as moving in great,"},{"time":275000,"text":"unhurried circles."},{"time":277000,"text":"It's always renewing and refreshing itself."},{"time":279000,"text":"Whereas in the West, time is linear."},{"time":281000,"text":"It's a finite resource;"},{"time":283000,"text":"it's always draining away."},{"time":285000,"text":"You either use it, or lose it."},{"time":287000,"text":"\"Time is money,\" as Benjamin Franklin said."},{"time":290000,"text":"And I think what that does to us psychologically"},{"time":292000,"text":"is it creates an equation."},{"time":294000,"text":"Time is scarce, so what do we do?"},{"time":296000,"text":"Well -- well, we speed up, don't we?"},{"time":298000,"text":"We try and do more and more with less and less time."},{"time":300000,"text":"We turn every moment of every day"},{"time":302000,"text":"into a race to the finish line --"},{"time":304000,"text":"a finish line, incidentally, that we never reach,"},{"time":307000,"text":"but a finish line nonetheless."},{"time":309000,"text":"And I guess that the question is,"},{"time":311000,"text":"is it possible to break free from that mindset?"},{"time":313000,"text":"And thankfully, the answer is yes, because"},{"time":315000,"text":"what I discovered, when I began looking around, that there is"},{"time":317000,"text":"a global backlash against this culture that"},{"time":320000,"text":"tells us that faster is always better, and that busier is best."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"Right across the world, people are doing the unthinkable:"},{"time":326000,"text":"they're slowing down, and finding that,"},{"time":328000,"text":"although conventional wisdom tells you that if you slow down, you're road kill,"},{"time":331000,"text":"the opposite turns out to be true:"},{"time":333000,"text":"that by slowing down at the right moments,"},{"time":335000,"text":"people find that they do everything better."},{"time":337000,"text":"They eat better; they make love better; they exercise better;"},{"time":340000,"text":"they work better; they live better."},{"time":343000,"text":"And, in this kind of cauldron"},{"time":346000,"text":"of moments and places and acts of deceleration,"},{"time":349000,"text":"lie what a lot of people now refer to as"},{"time":352000,"text":"the \"International Slow Movement.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":354000,"text":"Now if you'll permit me a small act of hypocrisy,"},{"time":359000,"text":"I'll just give you a very quick overview of"},{"time":362000,"text":"what's going on inside the Slow Movement. If you think of food,"},{"time":365000,"text":"many of you will have heard of the Slow Food movement."},{"time":367000,"text":"Started in Italy, but has spread across the world,"},{"time":369000,"text":"and now has 100,000 members"},{"time":371000,"text":"in 50 countries."},{"time":373000,"text":"And it's driven by a very simple and sensible message,"},{"time":376000,"text":"which is that we get more pleasure and more health"},{"time":379000,"text":"from our food when we"},{"time":381000,"text":"cultivate, cook and consume it at a reasonable pace."},{"time":385000,"text":"I think also the explosion of"},{"time":387000,"text":"the organic farming movement, and the renaissance of farmers' markets,"},{"time":390000,"text":"are other illustrations"},{"time":393000,"text":"of the fact that people are desperate to get away from"},{"time":396000,"text":"eating and cooking and cultivating their food"},{"time":398000,"text":"on an industrial timetable."},{"time":400000,"text":"They want to get back to slower rhythms."},{"time":403000,"text":"And out of the Slow Food movement has grown something"},{"time":406000,"text":"called the Slow Cities movement, which has started in Italy,"},{"time":409000,"text":"but has spread right across Europe and beyond."},{"time":411000,"text":"And in this, towns"},{"time":413000,"text":"begin to rethink how they organize the urban landscape,"},{"time":416000,"text":"so that people are encouraged to slow down"},{"time":419000,"text":"and smell the roses and connect with one another."},{"time":421000,"text":"So they might curb traffic,"},{"time":423000,"text":"or put in a park bench, or some green space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"And in some ways, these changes add up to more than the sum of their parts,"},{"time":429000,"text":"because I think when a Slow City becomes officially a Slow City,"},{"time":432000,"text":"it's kind of like a philosophical declaration."},{"time":434000,"text":"It's saying to the rest of world, and to the people in that town,"},{"time":437000,"text":"that we believe that in the 21st century,"},{"time":439000,"text":"\nslowness has a role to play."},{"time":443000,"text":"In medicine, I think a lot of people are deeply disillusioned"},{"time":445000,"text":"with the kind of quick-fix mentality"},{"time":447000,"text":"you find in conventional medicine."},{"time":449000,"text":"And millions of them around the world are turning"},{"time":451000,"text":"to complementary and alternative forms of medicine,"},{"time":454000,"text":"which tend to tap into sort of"},{"time":456000,"text":"slower, gentler, more holistic forms of healing."},{"time":459000,"text":"Now, obviously the jury is out on many of these complementary therapies,"},{"time":462000,"text":"and I personally doubt that the coffee enema"},{"time":465000,"text":"will ever, you know, gain mainstream approval."},{"time":468000,"text":"But other treatments"},{"time":470000,"text":"such as acupuncture and massage, and even just relaxation,"},{"time":473000,"text":"clearly have some kind of benefit."},{"time":475000,"text":"And blue-chip medical colleges everywhere"},{"time":477000,"text":"are starting to study these things to find out how they work,"},{"time":480000,"text":"and what we might learn from them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482000,"text":"Sex. There's an awful lot of fast sex around, isn't there?"},{"time":484000,"text":"I was coming to --"},{"time":487000,"text":"well -- no pun intended there."},{"time":490000,"text":"I was making my way, let's say, slowly to Oxford,"},{"time":493000,"text":"and I went through a news agent, and I saw a magazine,"},{"time":495000,"text":"a men's magazine, and it said on the front,"},{"time":497000,"text":"\"How to bring your partner to orgasm in 30 seconds.\""},{"time":500000,"text":"So, you know, even sex"},{"time":502000,"text":"is on a stopwatch these days."},{"time":504000,"text":"Now, you know,"},{"time":506000,"text":"I like a quickie as much as the next person,"},{"time":508000,"text":"but I think that there's an awful lot to be gained"},{"time":511000,"text":"from slow sex -- from slowing down in the bedroom."},{"time":513000,"text":"You know, you tap into that -- those deeper,"},{"time":516000,"text":"sort of, psychological, emotional, spiritual currents,"},{"time":519000,"text":"and you get a better orgasm with the buildup."},{"time":522000,"text":"You can get more bang for your buck, let's say."},{"time":524000,"text":"I mean, the Pointer Sisters said it most eloquently, didn't they,"},{"time":527000,"text":"when they sang the praises of \"a lover with a slow hand.\""},{"time":530000,"text":"Now, we all laughed at Sting"},{"time":532000,"text":"a few years ago when he went Tantric,"},{"time":534000,"text":"but you fast-forward a few years, and now you find couples of all ages"},{"time":537000,"text":"flocking to workshops, or maybe just"},{"time":539000,"text":"on their own in their own bedrooms, finding ways"},{"time":542000,"text":"to put on the brakes and have better sex."},{"time":545000,"text":"And of course, in Italy where -- I mean, Italians always seem to know"},{"time":547000,"text":"where to find their pleasure --"},{"time":549000,"text":"they've launched an official Slow Sex movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553000,"text":"The workplace."},{"time":555000,"text":"Right across much of the world --"},{"time":557000,"text":"North America being a notable exception --"},{"time":559000,"text":"working hours have been coming down."},{"time":561000,"text":"And Europe is an example of that,"},{"time":563000,"text":"and people finding that their quality of life improves"},{"time":566000,"text":"as they're working less, and also"},{"time":568000,"text":"that their hourly productivity goes up."},{"time":570000,"text":"Now, clearly there are problems with"},{"time":572000,"text":"the 35-hour workweek in France --"},{"time":574000,"text":"too much, too soon, too rigid."},{"time":576000,"text":"But other countries in Europe, notably the Nordic countries,"},{"time":579000,"text":"are showing that it's possible"},{"time":581000,"text":"to have a kick-ass economy"},{"time":583000,"text":"without being a workaholic."},{"time":585000,"text":"And Norway, Sweden,"},{"time":587000,"text":"Denmark and Finland now rank"},{"time":589000,"text":"among the top six most competitive nations on Earth,"},{"time":592000,"text":"and they work the kind of hours that would make the average American"},{"time":594000,"text":"weep with envy."},{"time":596000,"text":"And if you go beyond sort of the country level,"},{"time":599000,"text":"down at the micro-company level,"},{"time":601000,"text":"more and more companies now are realizing"},{"time":602000,"text":"that they need to allow their staff"},{"time":604000,"text":"either to work fewer hours or just to unplug --"},{"time":606000,"text":"to take a lunch break, or to go sit in a quiet room,"},{"time":610000,"text":"to switch off their Blackberrys and laptops -- you at the back --"},{"time":614000,"text":"mobile phones,"},{"time":616000,"text":"during the work day or on the weekend, so that they have time to recharge"},{"time":619000,"text":"and for the brain to slide into that"},{"time":621000,"text":"kind of creative mode of thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"It's not just, though, these days,"},{"time":628000,"text":"adults who overwork, though, is it? It's children, too."},{"time":631000,"text":"I'm 37, and my childhood ended in the mid-'80s,"},{"time":634000,"text":"and I look at kids now, and I'm just amazed by the way they"},{"time":636000,"text":"race around with more homework,"},{"time":638000,"text":"more tutoring, more extracurriculars"},{"time":640000,"text":"than we would ever have conceived of a generation ago."},{"time":643000,"text":"And some of the most heartrending emails"},{"time":645000,"text":"that I get on my website"},{"time":647000,"text":"are actually from adolescents"},{"time":650000,"text":"hovering on the edge of burnout, pleading with me"},{"time":652000,"text":"to write to their parents,"},{"time":654000,"text":"to help them slow down, to help them get off this"},{"time":657000,"text":"full-throttle treadmill."},{"time":660000,"text":"But thankfully, there is a backlash there in parenting as well,"},{"time":662000,"text":"and you're finding that, you know, towns in the United States"},{"time":664000,"text":"are now banding together and banning extracurriculars"},{"time":667000,"text":"on a particular day of the month, so that people can,"},{"time":669000,"text":"you know, decompress and have some family time, and slow down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"Homework is another thing. There are homework bans"},{"time":677000,"text":"springing up all over the developed world"},{"time":679000,"text":"in schools which had been piling on the homework for years,"},{"time":682000,"text":"and now they're discovering that less can be more."},{"time":684000,"text":"So there was a case up in Scotland recently"},{"time":686000,"text":"where a fee-paying, high-achieving private school"},{"time":688000,"text":"banned homework"},{"time":690000,"text":"for everyone under the age of 13,"},{"time":692000,"text":"and the high-achieving parents freaked out and said,"},{"time":694000,"text":"\"What are you -- you know, our kids will fall\" -- the headmaster said,"},{"time":696000,"text":"\"No, no, your children need to slow down at the end of the day.\""},{"time":699000,"text":"And just this last month, the exam results came in,"},{"time":702000,"text":"and in math, science, marks went up 20 percent"},{"time":705000,"text":"on average last year."},{"time":707000,"text":"And I think what's very revealing is that"},{"time":709000,"text":"the elite universities, who are often cited as the reason"},{"time":712000,"text":"that people drive their kids and hothouse them so much,"},{"time":714000,"text":"are starting to notice the caliber of students"},{"time":717000,"text":"coming to them is falling. These kids have wonderful marks;"},{"time":720000,"text":"they have CVs jammed with extracurriculars,"},{"time":723000,"text":"to the point that would make your eyes water."},{"time":725000,"text":"But they lack spark; they lack"},{"time":727000,"text":"the ability to think creatively and think outside --"},{"time":729000,"text":"they don't know how to dream. And so what these Ivy League schools,"},{"time":732000,"text":"and Oxford and Cambridge and so on, are starting to send a message"},{"time":734000,"text":"to parents and students that they need to put on the brakes a little bit."},{"time":737000,"text":"And in Harvard, for instance, they send out"},{"time":740000,"text":"a letter to undergraduates -- freshmen --"},{"time":743000,"text":"telling them that they'll get more out of life, and more out of Harvard,"},{"time":746000,"text":"if they put on the brakes, if they do less,"},{"time":748000,"text":"but give time to things, the time that things need,"},{"time":751000,"text":"to enjoy them, to savor them."},{"time":753000,"text":"And even if they sometimes do nothing at all."},{"time":755000,"text":"And that letter is called -- very revealing, I think --"},{"time":757000,"text":"\"Slow Down!\" -- with an exclamation mark on the end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"So wherever you look, the message, it seems to me, is the same:"},{"time":763000,"text":"that less is very often more,"},{"time":765000,"text":"that slower is very often"},{"time":768000,"text":"better. But that said, of course,"},{"time":770000,"text":"it's not that easy to slow down, is it?"},{"time":772000,"text":"I mean, you heard that I got a speeding ticket"},{"time":774000,"text":"while I was researching my book on the benefits of slowness,"},{"time":776000,"text":"and that's true, but that's not all of it."},{"time":778000,"text":"I was actually en route to a dinner"},{"time":780000,"text":"held by Slow Food at the time."},{"time":782000,"text":"And if that's not shaming enough, I got that ticket in Italy."},{"time":785000,"text":"And if any of you have ever driven on an Italian highway,"},{"time":788000,"text":"you'll have a pretty good idea of how fast I was going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":793000,"text":"But why is it so hard to slow down?"},{"time":795000,"text":"I think there are various reasons."},{"time":797000,"text":"One is that speed is fun, you know, speed is sexy."},{"time":800000,"text":"It's all that adrenaline rush. It's hard to give it up."},{"time":803000,"text":"I think there's a kind of metaphysical dimension --"},{"time":805000,"text":"that speed becomes a way of walling ourselves off"},{"time":807000,"text":"from the bigger, deeper questions."},{"time":809000,"text":"We fill our head with distraction, with busyness,"},{"time":811000,"text":"so that we don't have to ask,"},{"time":813000,"text":"am I well? Am I happy? Are my children growing up right?"},{"time":816000,"text":"Are politicians making good decisions on my behalf?"},{"time":820000,"text":"Another reason -- although I think, perhaps, the most powerful reason --"},{"time":822000,"text":"why we find it hard to slow down is the cultural taboo"},{"time":825000,"text":"that we've erected against slowing down."},{"time":828000,"text":"\"Slow\" is a dirty word in our culture."},{"time":830000,"text":"It's a byword for \"lazy,\" \"slacker,\""},{"time":832000,"text":"for being somebody who gives up."},{"time":834000,"text":"You know, \"he's a bit slow.\" It's actually synonymous"},{"time":836000,"text":"with being stupid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839000,"text":"I guess what the Slow Movement -- the purpose of the Slow Movement,"},{"time":841000,"text":"or its main goal, really, is to tackle that taboo,"},{"time":843000,"text":"and to say that yes,"},{"time":846000,"text":"sometimes slow is not the answer,"},{"time":848000,"text":"that there is such a thing as \"bad slow.\""},{"time":850000,"text":"You know, I got stuck on the M25,"},{"time":852000,"text":"which is a ring road around London, recently,"},{"time":854000,"text":"and spent three-and-a-half hours there. And I can tell you,"},{"time":856000,"text":"that's really bad slow."},{"time":858000,"text":"But the new idea,"},{"time":860000,"text":"the sort of revolutionary idea, of the Slow Movement,"},{"time":862000,"text":"is that there is such a thing as \"good slow,\" too."},{"time":864000,"text":"And good slow is, you know, taking the time"},{"time":866000,"text":"to eat a meal with your family, with the TV switched off."},{"time":869000,"text":"Or taking the time to look at a problem from all angles"},{"time":872000,"text":"in the office to make the best decision"},{"time":874000,"text":"at work."},{"time":876000,"text":"Or even simply just taking the time"},{"time":878000,"text":"to slow down"},{"time":880000,"text":"and savor your life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882000,"text":"Now, one of the things that I found most uplifting"},{"time":885000,"text":"about all of this stuff that's happened around the book"},{"time":888000,"text":"since it came out, is the reaction to it."},{"time":891000,"text":"And I knew that when my book on slowness came out,"},{"time":893000,"text":"it would be welcomed by the New Age brigade,"},{"time":895000,"text":"but it's also been taken up, with great gusto,"},{"time":898000,"text":"by the corporate world -- you know,"},{"time":900000,"text":"business press, but also"},{"time":902000,"text":"big companies and leadership organizations."},{"time":904000,"text":"Because people at the top of the chain, people like you, I think,"},{"time":907000,"text":"are starting to realize that there's too much"},{"time":909000,"text":"speed in the system,"},{"time":911000,"text":"there's too much busyness, and it's time to find,"},{"time":914000,"text":"or get back to that lost art of shifting gears."},{"time":918000,"text":"Another encouraging sign, I think,"},{"time":920000,"text":"is that it's not just in the developed world"},{"time":922000,"text":"that this idea's been taken up. In the developing world,"},{"time":925000,"text":"in countries that are on the verge of making that leap"},{"time":927000,"text":"into first world status -- China, Brazil,"},{"time":929000,"text":"Thailand, Poland, and so on --"},{"time":931000,"text":"these countries have embraced the idea of the Slow Movement,"},{"time":934000,"text":"many people in them, and there's a debate going on"},{"time":937000,"text":"in their media, on the streets."},{"time":939000,"text":"Because I think they're looking at the West, and they're saying,"},{"time":941000,"text":"\"Well, we like that aspect of what you've got,"},{"time":944000,"text":"but we're not so sure about that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":946000,"text":"So all of that said, is it,"},{"time":948000,"text":"I guess, is it possible?"},{"time":951000,"text":"That's really the main question before us today. Is it possible"},{"time":954000,"text":"to slow down? And"},{"time":956000,"text":"I'm happy to be able to say to you"},{"time":958000,"text":"that the answer is a resounding yes."},{"time":960000,"text":"And I present myself as Exhibit A,"},{"time":963000,"text":"a kind of reformed and rehabilitated"},{"time":966000,"text":"speed-aholic."},{"time":968000,"text":"I still love speed. You know, I live in London,"},{"time":970000,"text":"and I work as a journalist,"},{"time":972000,"text":"and I enjoy the buzz and the busyness,"},{"time":974000,"text":"and the adrenaline rush that comes from both of those things."},{"time":976000,"text":"I play squash and ice hockey,"},{"time":978000,"text":"two very fast sports, and I wouldn't give them up for the world."},{"time":982000,"text":"But I've also, over the last year or so,"},{"time":985000,"text":"got in touch with my inner tortoise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":987000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":988000,"text":"And what that means is that"},{"time":990000,"text":"I no longer"},{"time":993000,"text":"overload myself gratuitously."},{"time":996000,"text":"My default mode is no longer"},{"time":999000,"text":"to be a rush-aholic."},{"time":1002000,"text":"I no longer hear"},{"time":1004000,"text":"time's winged chariot drawing near,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"or at least not as much as I did before."},{"time":1008000,"text":"I can actually hear it now, because I see my time is ticking off."},{"time":1012000,"text":"And the upshot of all of that is that"},{"time":1014000,"text":"I actually feel a lot happier, healthier,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"more productive than I ever have."},{"time":1020000,"text":"I feel like I'm living"},{"time":1022000,"text":"my life rather than actually just racing through it."},{"time":1026000,"text":"And perhaps, the most important"},{"time":1028000,"text":"measure of the success of this"},{"time":1030000,"text":"is that I feel that my relationships are a lot deeper,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"richer, stronger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035000,"text":"And for me, I guess, the litmus test"},{"time":1038000,"text":"for whether this would work, and what it would mean,"},{"time":1040000,"text":"was always going to be bedtime stories, because that's sort of where"},{"time":1043000,"text":"the journey began. And there too the news is"},{"time":1046000,"text":"rosy. You know,"},{"time":1048000,"text":"at the end of the day, I go into my son's room."},{"time":1050000,"text":"I don't wear a watch. I switch off my computer,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"so I can't hear the email pinging into the basket,"},{"time":1054000,"text":"and I just slow down to his pace and we read."},{"time":1058000,"text":"And because children have their own tempo and internal clock,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"they don't do quality time,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"where you schedule 10 minutes for them to open up to you."},{"time":1065000,"text":"They need you to move at their rhythm."},{"time":1068000,"text":"I find that 10 minutes into a story, you know,"},{"time":1070000,"text":"my son will suddenly say, \"You know,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"something happened in the playground today that really bothered me.\""},{"time":1074000,"text":"And we'll go off and have a conversation on that."},{"time":1077000,"text":"And I now find that bedtime stories"},{"time":1080000,"text":"used to be"},{"time":1082000,"text":"a box on my to-do list, something that I dreaded,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"because it was so slow and I had to get through it quickly."},{"time":1087000,"text":"It's become my reward at the end of the day,"},{"time":1089000,"text":"something I really cherish."},{"time":1091000,"text":"And I have a kind of Hollywood ending"},{"time":1093000,"text":"to my talk this afternoon,"},{"time":1095000,"text":"which goes a little bit like this:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1097000,"text":"a few months ago, I was getting ready to go on"},{"time":1100000,"text":"another book tour, and I had my bags packed."},{"time":1103000,"text":"I was downstairs by the front door, and I was waiting for a taxi,"},{"time":1106000,"text":"and my son came down the stairs and"},{"time":1108000,"text":"he'd made a card for me. And he was carrying it."},{"time":1110000,"text":"He'd gone and stapled two cards, very like these, together,"},{"time":1112000,"text":"and put a sticker of his favorite"},{"time":1115000,"text":"character, Tintin, on the front."},{"time":1117000,"text":"And he said to me,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"or he handed this to me, and I read it,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"and it said, \"To Daddy, love Benjamin.\""},{"time":1123000,"text":"And I thought, \"Aw, that's really sweet."},{"time":1126000,"text":"Is that a good luck on the book tour card?\""},{"time":1129000,"text":"And he said, \"No, no, no, Daddy -- this is a card"},{"time":1131000,"text":"for being the best story reader in the world.\""},{"time":1133000,"text":"And I thought, \"Yeah, you know, this slowing down thing really does work.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1136000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}